column1: <th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="GP" tooltip="Games Played - The number of games a player or team has played.">GP</th>
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="W" tooltip="Wins - The number of games the player or team has won.">W</th>
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="L" tooltip="Losses - The number of games the player or team has lost.">L</th>
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="MIN" tooltip="Minutes - The number of minutes a player or team has played.">MIN</th>
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="FGM" tooltip="Field Goals Made - The number of field goals that a player or team has made. This includes both 2 pointers and 3 pointers.">FGM</th>
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="FGA" tooltip="Field Goals Attempted - The number of field goals that a player or team has attempted. This includes both 2 pointers and 3 pointers.">FGA</th>

<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="FG_PCT" tooltip="Field Goal Percentage - The percentage of field goals that a player makes. The formula to determine field goal percentage is: Field Goals Made/Field Goals Attempted.">FG%</th>
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="FG3M" tooltip="3 Point Field Goals Made - The number of 3 point field goals that a player or team has made.">3PM</th>
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="FG3A" tooltip="3 Point Field Goals Attempted - The number of 3 point field goals that a player or team has attempted.">3PA</th>

<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="FG3_PCT" tooltip="3 Point Field Goal Percentage - The percentage of 3 point field goals that a player or team has made. The formula to determine 3 point field goal percentage is: 3 Point Field Goals Made/3 Point Field Goals Attempted.">3P%</th>
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="FTM" tooltip="Free Throws Made - The number of free throws that a player or team has successfully made.">FTM</th>
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="FTA" tooltip="Free Throws Attempted - The number of free throws that a player or team has taken.">FTA</th>

<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="FT_PCT" tooltip="Free Throw Percentage - The percentage of free throws that a player or team has made. The formula to determine free throw percentage is: Free Throws Made/Free Throws Attempted.">FT%</th>
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="OREB" tooltip="Offensive Rebounds - The number of rebounds a player or team has collected while they were on offense.">OREB</th>
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="DREB" tooltip="Defensive Rebounds - The number of rebounds a player or team has collected while they were on defense.">DREB</th>

<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="REB" tooltip="Rebounds - A rebound occurs when a player recovers the ball after a missed shot. This statistic is the number of total rebounds a player or team has collected on either offense or defense.">REB</th>
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="AST" tooltip="Assists - An assist occurs when a player completes a pass to a teammate that directly leads to a made field goal.">AST</th>
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="TOV" tooltip="Turnovers - A turnover occurs when the team on offense loses the ball to the defense.">TOV</th>
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="STL" tooltip="Steals - A steal occurs when a defensive player takes the ball from a player on offense
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="BLK" tooltip="Blocks - A block occurs when an offensive player attempts a shot
column2: and the defense player tips the ball

column1: <th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="PF" tooltip="Personal Fouls - The total number of fouls that a player or team has committed.">PF</th>

<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="DD2" tooltip="Double Doubles - A player records a Double Double when they record 10 or more units in two stat categories. A Double Double is most commonly recorded in the categories of points

<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="TD3" tooltip="Triple Doubles - A player records a Triple Double when they record 10 or more units in three different stat categories. A Triple Double is most commonly recorded in the categories of points
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="PTS" tooltip="Points - The number of points a player or team has scored. A point is scored when a player makes a basket.">PTS</th>
<th class="sortable cf ng-scope" field="PLUS_MINUS" tooltip="Plus/Minus - The point differential of the score for a player while on the court. For a team
column2: it is how much they are winning or losing by.">+/-</th>
